                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00–N/74: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-17T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 17, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>230. The surrender of France has served to strengthen materially the hands of the
                    pro-Nazi elements here and that the Government is now faced with a situation
                    that might conceivably get out of hand. Without wishing to appear to exaggerate
                    the gravity of conditions, I feel strongly that our Government should take
                    prompt and energetic action to meet this danger.</p>
                <p>[Here follows a report of press comment.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
